This post serves as a simple test of image handling in Markdoc.
It demonstrates how images can be included and optimized within the content.

This is a landscape image without a caption:

![Landscape Image](https://share.kadykov.com/2024/12/26/DSC_2884.jpg)

This is a landscape image with a caption:

![Landscape Image with Caption](https://share.kadykov.com/2024/12/26/DSC_2884.jpg "This is a caption for the landscape image")

This is a portrait image without a caption:

![Portrait Image](https://share.kadykov.com/2024/03/10/DSC_2810.jpg)

This is a portrait image with a caption:

![Portrait Image with Caption](https://share.kadykov.com/2024/03/10/DSC_2810.jpg "This is a caption for the portrait image")

This is a landscape image with a very long caption that should wrap nicely within the content area. The caption is designed to demonstrate how text wraps around images in Markdoc, ensuring that even lengthy descriptions remain readable and visually appealing.

